---
description:
Application-wide error handling strategy.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Error Handling

Errors should educate, not frustrate.

Every error should have:

Cause

↓

Recovery

↓

Next Action

Never expose stack traces to users.

---

# Error Categories

Infrastructure

Network

Authentication

Validation

Business Logic

Permission

Unexpected

Each category requires a dedicated failure model.

---

# Domain Failures

Infrastructure errors must be converted into domain failures.

Never expose:

SocketException

DioException

FormatException

to presentation.

---

# User Messages

Messages should be:

Clear

Professional

Actionable

Avoid technical jargon.

Example:

Instead of:

"SocketException"

Use:

"Unable to connect. Check your internet connection."

---

# Retry

Allow retry only where appropriate.

Examples:

Network Requests

Downloads

Synchronization

Never automatically retry:

Payments

Exam submissions

Account deletion

---

# Global Error Handler

Create a centralized error handler.

Responsibilities:

- Logging
- Mapping
- Reporting
- Analytics

---

# Logging

Capture:

Stack Trace

Device

Version

Screen

API Endpoint

Never log:

Passwords

JWT

Personal data

---

# Empty vs Error

Differentiate between:

No data

and

Request failed

Never use the same screen.

---

# Validation

Validation belongs inside:

Application Layer

Domain Layer

Never inside Widgets.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Every async operation must expose:

Loading

Success

Empty

Error

Recovery Action